to the editor re the zoo is fiction but it might just spring to life pondicherry journal feb 20 about plans to create an actual zoo in pondicherry india inspired by the fictional one in the novel life of pi a devotee of a pondicherry ashram once surprised me by explaining that people have greater personal responsibility over animals than they have over one another the reason animals bereft of powers of reason are at the mercy of humans and thus merit our protection even the least advantaged people on the other hand are at least endowed with the tools to fend for themselves vis a vis other humans it would be a sad irony if a zoo were to be built in this city of spirituality solely to satisfy the expectations of western tourists who have read life of pi william miles boston feb 20 2003

